'''Level 505''' is the 506<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms.

<div id="l_desc" style="background: linear-gradient(225deg, #0a003e, black, black, black, #0a003e); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #0F005C; margin: 20px; padding: 15px;">
<span style="font-size:36px; color: #4f4cff"><center>'''Level Description'''</center></span>
{{Underline|4f4cff}}
{{Blurimage|caption=A photo of an attempted illumination of the path, flashlight used is estimated to have about 200 Lumens.|file=It is dark as hell in this funky ass dark ass room i am in bruh.png}}

Because of Level 505's abnormal darkness, it's nearly impossible to get a proper, visual documentation of the level, leaving the level's appearance unknown. Attempts at illuminating the level were made, but to no avail as illumination technology failed to light up the level. There are some known properties of the level however. The level majorly contains the smell of candle wax, and a little further in, reeks of rotting brick and marble. The material of the level aligns with its later smell as brick and marble. The brick applies to the walls and ground with the occasional carpet found on the ground, while the marble applies to the commonly found pillar. Level 505, despite its abnormal darkness, has an even stranger anomaly. Sounds within the level or caused by entities/humans are signified by colored "ripples". These ripples make navigation of the level easier, despite it's unusual dark. The edges of a ripple disappear when in contact with a solid object, which also assists with navigation greatly.


As previously mentioned, Level 505 has a strange property in which it is in perpetual darkness, this darkness cannot be lifted and it also appears to minorly alter the geometry of the level. Despite this, Wanderers are attempting to make a general map of the regions in the level. WIth the fact that sound ripples are able to be seen and tend to assist with navigation in general, mapping out the level is easy and efficient. Aside from that, wanderers that end up in this level have reported feeling many different emotions. What is strange however, is that these emotions can vary from a looming sense of dread, to pure relaxation. Due to the severely anomalous nature of the level, it is advised to remain cautious at all times. This level also contains entities unlike we've seen before. Their appearances are unknown, their intentions are unknown, and usually so are their locations due to the overwhelming darkness (of course, the sound ripples make it easier to semi-track them down). This entity (or entities) appear to be the main cause of this level's darkness. While it is unknown how to avoid it and its intentions, it appears all its effects are purely mental and aren't lasting.


But of course, Level 505's darkness is best compared to the embodiment of dread. While the mentality a wanderer may receive from the level proves otherwise, most wanderers say that even if feeling the benefits, they can only imagine there's something odd and inconsistent within the level. They have also stated that previous areas they have walked through may not be there when coming back which proves this level alters its geometry on a regular basis. Nonetheless, documenters have investigated if it could be a Class Theta level, and it was decided to keep a more "basic" class level called "Dark" until all information is collected. This phenomenon is also explained as "going into a place and forgetting why you were there" one explorer says. 


As of the most recent documentation update (June 5th, 2021), [[M.E.G.]] has not made many attempts to recognize this level due to its anomalous property. While it does seem that the level should grab M.E.G.'s attention, it is assumed that M.E.G. also does not have the relevant technology to subside the effects of the level. Aside from M.E.G.'s inattention, the documenters are hard at work attempting to figure out any and all information regarding Level 505. It has been decided that the level will be called: '''"Sanctuary."''' given its anomalous properties. This is likely a temporary name and will change later when more is learned about the level, until then, it is to be referred to as such.


The layout, the size (infinite/finite), and the visual properties of this level are not attainable at the current moment. While, the layout can get a general idea, the altering geometry makes it more tedious. However, what is known is that not all of it is just brick and marble. There is a confirmed place in the level that leads to a library of sorts. Books have been managed to be escorted outside of it and are actively attempting to decipher them to see if they could hold crucial information. As of currently, this is the only area in the level that can be deemed important, as no other area shares distinctive properties from the level's base form.

Many wanderers tend to have good experiences with this level, some wanderers that have explored in-depth a little more were found disliking and unwanting to return. This likely withholds correlation to the '''Darkness Entity''' that was mentioned precedingly but was not named. Environmentally, this level appears to be safe, stable and healing to some wanderers. It is unknown if the '''Darkness Entity''' is the only entity within the level, there have been no encounters or suspected encounters with other entities, yet it is still too early to say anything considering how much less this level is visually documented compared to many other levels. Documenters are still actively working on moving around and creating a map to help guide wanderers. As it stands, only the level itself is unable to be illuminated, external objects and people can. This likely means good things for the future of the level.


It is unlikely that there are any other entities inhabiting this level aside from the '''Darkness Entity'''. Much of the evidence collected supports the claim that the entity warded off the other entities. Researchers are working on deciphering what documenters observe and updates will be provided as soon as possible. 

Please understand that M.E.G. is not actively assisting with this specific level so documentation will be a little less professional. If you or someone you know has previously noclipped into this level and has something to share, it is encouraged to use [[BackOS]] and reach out at "lrc@back.com" to provide information and assist in documentation. Any and all help is appreciated!

This level was discovered in the month of January, 2016 and the most recent documentation update made to it was in the month of June, 2021. This level's discovery was on complete accident, and regarding the nature of entering and exiting the level, it is surprising the level is rather new. 
</div>
<div id="e_count" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a003e, black, black, black, #0a003e); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #0F005C; margin: 20px; padding: 15px;">
<span style="font-size:36px; color: #4f4cff"><center>'''Entities'''</center></span>
{{Underline|4f4cff}}

Currently there is only a speculated one entity to inhabit this level. No signs of other entities have been found.

<div id="e_1" style="background: linear-gradient(225deg, #b508ff, black, black, black, #b508ff); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #8e00cb; margin: 15px; padding: 10px;">
<span style="font-size:20px; color: #dd7fff"><center>'''Darkness Entity'''</center></span>

'''Because there is no official name to this entity, it is to be referred to as "Darkness Entity" until more information and research has been concluded upon it.'''

The Darkness Entity is the first (and possibly only) of its kind, found to reside in the entirety of Level 505. There is currently no appearance to this entity as it is impossible to observe one in regards to the entity's anomaly. The Darkness Entity is, however, presumed to be an all-powerfull being due to its abilities to alter an individual's psyche and controlling the level's base state. While it is not the first case of an entity being able to do as such, it is indeed a troublesome and rare case, considering that it not only is just the level's visuality, it also alters the geometry.

The psychological effects this entity may instill into wanderers ranges from slight itches in the noggin, the feeling of a "bump-in-the-night" sort of thing, slight paranoia, full paranoia (or impending doom), chills, feverish symptoms, and feeling of weakness in the limbs. The positive side-effects range from relaxation up to pure mental bliss. While it may not seem like much, if wandering in an especially dark level such as this one, these psychological effects tend to be amplified by tenfold and inflict an unforgettable experience for the wanderers. It is believed that if the entity is extracted from the level, it'll likely become a completely safe space for wanderers and allow colonies and outposts to thrive, as the darkness should also subside (more on this in Theories).

EST. Entity Count: 1

EST. Entity Location: Level 505.

EST. Entity Behavior: Neutral (Hostile to some, Passive to some)

EST. Entity Danger Level: 2/5

EST. Entity Provocations: Unknown

How To Avoid: If inside of Level 505, there is not much a wanderer can do to avoid it.

If Encountered, What To Do: Stay alert, there is no doubt it'll mess with a wanderer's brain.

</div>

</div>
<div id="u_areas" style="background: linear-gradient(225deg, #0a003e, black, black, black, #0a003e); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #0F005C; margin: 20px; padding: 15px;">
<span style="font-size:36px; color: #4f4cff"><center>'''Unique Areas'''</center></span>
{{Underline|4f4cff}}

Currently, it is difficult to say that there are many unique areas within this level. Documenters have only came across one confirmed unique area, with others being proven to be a side-effect of the Darkness Entity's abilities.

<div id="u_area1" style="background: linear-gradient(225deg, #b508ff, black, black, black, #b508ff); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #8e00cb; margin: 15px; padding: 10px;">
<span style="font-size:20px; color: #dd7fff"><center>'''The Library'''</center></span>

The Library is the only confirmed unique area and is known to be quite expansive. The Library itself appears to be made out of sanded down oak and pine and consists of a desk, bookshelves, and a staircase leading to two presumably locked doors. The books themselves have been extracted from the shelves and are being taken to the research department to decipher and understand. As for the location itself, it appears to shield from the Darkness Entity and seems habitable. There are no confirmations, however, that a colony may stand in a place like this. The Library itself poses no anomalous properties and is treated as just a normal library with books written in an unknown language. The Library smells sharply of wood and only has sounds of a fire crackling within its region. The fire has not been located, however, because of the lack of illumination in the level. This area could pose to be important in the future.

</div>
</div>
<div id="c_n_op" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a003e, black, black, black, #0a003e); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #0F005C; margin: 20px; padding: 15px;">
<span style="font-size:36px; color: #4f4cff"><center>'''Outposts, Bases, or Colonies'''</center></span>
{{Underline|4f4cff}}

No current outposts, bases, or colonies have been established in Level 505, but efforts are being made.

</div>
<div id="ent_n_ex" style="background: linear-gradient(225deg, #0a003e, black, black, black, #0a003e); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #0F005C; margin: 20px; padding: 15px;">
<span style="font-size:36px; color: #4f4cff"><center>'''Entrances and Exits'''</center></span>
