<div id="ent" style="background: linear-gradient(225deg, #b508ff, black, black, black, #b508ff); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #8e00cb; margin: 15px; padding: 10px;">
<span style="font-size:24px; color: #dd7fff"><center>'''Entrances'''</center></span>

* The most common entrance is from [[Level 6]]. Where if in an especially dark place, has a chance to lead to Level 505.
* Getting '''lost where the forest should go''' in [[Level 125]].
* Many more unconfirmed entrances to this level, all including churches within separate levels.
</div>
<div id="ex" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #b508ff, black, black, black, #b508ff); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #8e00cb; margin: 15px; padding: 10px;">
<span style="font-size:24px; color: #dd7fff"><center>'''Exits'''</center></span>

* It is possible to stumble across an unlocked door that will lead to a random level, most notably, [[Level 6]].
* Most other exits are derived from random chance of no-clipping.
** This level is heavily prone to being no-clipped into and no-clipped out of.
</div>
</div>

<div id="theor" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0a003e, black, black, black, #0a003e); border-radius: 5px; border: 5px solid #0F005C; margin: 20px; padding: 15px;">
<span style="font-size:36px; color: #4f4cff"><center>'''Theories'''</center></span>

'''DISCLAIMER: THIS IS ALL SIMPLY SPECULATION, DOCUMENTATION EITHER DOES NOT PROVE OR SUPPORT ANYTHING STATED IN THIS PART OF THE PAGE OR MINIMALLY SUPPORTS IT!'''

There are many speculations regarding this level, its phenomena, and its entity (entities).

The most common one is the belief that the entity residing within the level is the cause of the phenomena and that the level could turn into a habitable, visual, region if the entity is killed or extracted. While, this part may have been touched upon in documentation, it is a quite supported theory and is believed to be true unless proven otherwise. This is the only "speculation" that has supporting details.

Some other beliefs include the main existence of other entities in the level. While there is for sure a main entity that is unobserved and unknown, there could be other entities (unknown or discovered) that reside in the level. The other side of this theory is that there are no other entities in this level due to them being "warded off" etc. etc. It is important to note that the '''Darkness Entity''' cannot physically do anything (as of current observation), so the idea behind it warding off other entities is an interesting claim. It is not impossible, however.
</div>

